        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 15 at 1:46PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 145 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Ballard, or near Ash Flat, moving east at 65 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Heart...                          Franklin...
Smithville...                     Fryatt...
Agnos...                          Shannon...
Kittle...                         Nelsonville...
Annieville...                     Elnora...
Dalton...                         Horseshoe Bend...
Evening Shade...                  Imboden...
Glencoe...                        Mount Pleasant...
Warm Springs...                   Poughkeepsie...
Sidney...                         Eleven Point...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
